seqprinter
----------

Flexible and extensible pretty-printing of genomic sequences, given a bed file
and a fasta file.

Includes numbers with tick marks and sequence, and then applies any additional
user-specified functions to generate additional "tracks".

Originally written to help identify single bp positions within overlapping CTCF
binding sites to choose for experimental follow-up but generalized for other uses.

Example usage (uses MotifPrinter, which is a subclass of BasePrinter)::

    >>> from seqprint.SeqPrinter import MotifPrinter
    >>> from seqprint.helpers import data_file
    >>> # get example data
    >>> regions = data_file('regions.bed')
    >>> fasta = data_file('chr11_subset.fa')
    >>> jaspar_file = data_file('ctcf.jaspar')
    >>> jaspar_thresh = 1.5
    >>> x = MotifPrinter(regions, fasta, jaspar_file=jaspar_file,
    ...     jaspar_thresh=jaspar_thresh)
    >>> x.printseq()

